    "summary": "As from Septemer 1st 2022 I have been appointed Professor of Health Care Ethics at the Theological University Kampen | Utrecht on behalf of the Prof. G.A. Lindeboom Institute for medical ethics. \nI combine this function with my work as a health scientist and health ethicist at the Radboud University Medical Center Nijmegen. \n\nSince 2019 I have been part of the Moral Compass Project at the Protestant Theological University (PThU) in Groningen and Amsterdam. Our research is about morality and euthanasia. \n\nSince august 2013 I have been working as a Senior Researcher and as staff member at IQ Healthcare, Radboud University Medical Centre in Nijmegen; both as a Health Scientist and as an (Clinical) Ethicist. \nAt IQ Healthcare, my work mainly focuses on three research themes: a) End of Life Care; b) Geographical variation in health care, and c) Health System Ethics. \n\nPreviously, I followed the Master of Applied Ethics at the University of Utrecht in september 2013, which I accomplished in the summer of 2015. \n\nFrom 2011 until 2013 I was a senior manager at KPMG Plexus in Breukelen, The Netherlands. My specialties: Quality of care, (policy) research, indicators, benchmarking, long term care, care for the elderly, primary care.\n\nFrom april 2010 until august 2011 I was director of The Lindeboom Institute for Health Care Ethics. Here, I did several studies (eg. in palliative care) and published (scientific) articles. \n\nFrom 2005 until 2010 I worked as a Senior Consultant at Plexus, a leading consutancy in health care. Here, I developed quality indicators in the area of mental health care, geriatric care, maternity care etc. Lately, I've been doing a lot of work in primary care.The creation of the \"Plexus-primary care-benchmark\" was one of my latest projects before my period at the Lindeboom Institute.\n\nFrom 2003-2008 I worked as a PhD-student at the Institute of Health Policy and Management, Erasmus University Medical Centre, Rotterdam\n\nFrom 2000-2003 I worked as a junior researcher at the Institute of Health Policy and Management, Erasmus University Medical Centre, Rotterdam.\n\nIn 1999/2000 I was a business analyst at the health care consulting group of Deloitte & Touche\n\nSpecialties: Health care quality, quality indicators, benchmarking, Medical Ethics, Health System Ethics",
